store in pahrump is one of hundreds of locations across the country that has gone through a rebranding—bringing in additional products and technology upgrades that increase access to a wider variety of merchandise“with the integration of technology into our shopping experience we’re able to offer a greatly improved shopping experience” said lennie hill a district manager of the sears hometown stores in nevada in a written statement “customers will be able to search and compare any combination of appliances they can think of through our instore kiosks…”as part of the refresh the local store at  e highway  suite  added “more brands and an improved presentation” sears hometown and outlet stores inc shos said in a news release nationwide sears hometown is also changing its branding to america’s appliance experts“the stores’ appliances are also focused on innovative and valueadded products from lg electronics inc general electric co whirlpool maytag kitchenaid samsung electronics co and kenmore” according to the companysears hometown also provided employees with comprehensive training which included “brandspecific selling certification” the company announced in a news releasecorporate refresh and structurethe new look in pahrump was announced by sears hometown and outlet stores in june along with another location in fallon overall the company has updated more than  locations or more than  percent of its portfolio as of a june  news release the companywide initiative began in the upgrade data includes corporate locations along with independent franchise stores with the pahrump location being one of thosegenerally franchise owners are responsible for operating costs such as rent and payroll but not its inventory according to information on the sears hometown corporate websitesears hometown provides the merchandise for the store’s operator which averages  to  along with supplying marketing efforts franchisees are then paid a commission for sales along with collecting revenue from protection agreements credit offerings and delivery and installation servicesfranchise owners must have a minimum of  cash and a positive net worth of at least  to open a new store options for adding a sears hometown label to an existing business which already has a physical location are also availablesears hometown store closingssears hometown which spun off in  from sears holdings corp owner of sears department stores has traveled down a similar path with store closure announcements becoming a regular occurrencesears hometown and outlet stores operated  stores across  states and puerto rico and bermuda as of april  that number includes holdings by independent dealers and franchisees as well according to a news release from sears hometown corporatethat’s down from the  locations the company held in early  nearly a  percent decrease information from a securities and exchange commission filing in february  showeda large portion of store closings occurred in the company’s  fiscal year based on a net loss of  locations about  percent of the company’s closures occurred during fiscal year  which ended in january the company shuttered  locations in that period—though  new stores came online as wellnot all the information is negativepositive rifts occurred during the first quarter for sears hometown stores that had gone through a rebranding to the america’s appliance expertsaccording to a first quarter earnings report statistics showed sales on appliances with the new branding were  basis points above stores that hadn’t converted which is equal to about  percent more salesin may sears hometown decided that it would close more stores to better use its capital and reduce costs the company said the company which operates two separate labels sears hometown and its outlet stores label planned to shutter  stores  hometown and  outlet locationssears hometown also made plans to purchase back  franchise locations in the first quarter and the company could make plans for this type of deal in the future“we view reacquisitions of franchiseeoperated stores that are not meeting our performance expectations as an important part of our longterm strategy” the company stated in an earnings report at the end of aprilstate of retail across the nationsears holdings owner of sears and kmart stores has closed many of its stores since  as well the iconic brand that once did business through catalog orders has gone from  fullline sears locations to  at the end of the first quarterthe company also plans to close more than  sears stores by the end of some of its other holdings have also been reduced in size with kmart sitting at  locations at the end of the first quarter that’s a decrease of more than  percent in locations since  when there were more than  kmart stores in operationthis is not an unusual tale in today’s market as retailers have announced closure of thousands of stores in  alone according to fung global retail technology the us should expect more than  retail locations to close in names such as payless shoes and rue inc announced entry into chapter  bankruptcy in  just those two retailers alone account for more than  store closingsother labels closing locations include guess inc bebe stores inc and abercrombie fitchcontact reporter jeffrey meehan at jmeehanpvtimescom on twitter pvtimesmost popularman appears in court to face charges in pahrump girl’s death graffiti sprayed on the new tractor supply co store in pahrump pahrump man  dies in dump truck crash pahrumparea fire crews see busy week valley electric association transmission line sale still on hold tweets by pvtimes    pahrump sears hometown store rebrands  pv times  friday july  pv timespv timesfacebooktwitterrsssearch this site        posted july    ampahrump sears hometown store rebrandspahrump sears hometown store rebrandsjeffrey meehanpahrump valley times sears hometown store at  e highway  suite  on july   the pahrump store is one of hundreds across the nation to be rebranded